					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djkaktus" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1888434); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1888434&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610164135" alt="djkaktus" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1888434)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djkaktus" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1888434); return false;" >djkaktus</a></span> <span class="odate time_1510123178 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">08 Nov 2017 06:39</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3628187">
									

<p>Realistically this is about as canon an interpretation of how &quot;consensus reality&quot; is determined as anything I've seen thus far. Almost makes you wonder if the Overseers aren't there for literally anything else <em>but</em> determining the consensus. Really spooky stuff.</p>
<p>I really enjoy this. The end of the last note has a very &quot;The Man At The Threshold&quot; vibe at the end of it, albeit a little less sinister than that. Either way, there's something pretty unsettling about this all the way through, and strikes plenty of high points for me.</p>
<p>Goodness, we're going to need to start thinking about a better way to organize the 001 list at this rate.</p>

							</div>

								
					
